in by 1731","body":"A tailor by trade and extensive landholder at Farmington, he rose through the militia ranks — Ensign 1717, Lieutenant 1723, Captain by May 1731 of the 2nd Company Trainband. He also served as Company Clerk in 1714, collector of the minister's rate 1698-1700, constable for several years, and town representative in 1726.","number":2},{"category":"legacy","header":"Five surviving sons divided 2500 pounds, 1763","body":"His will was dated October 1740 and proved March 1756. Seven years later in 1763 his last five surviving sons divided his Farmington estate — approximately £2,500 among themselves as sole heirs, an unusually concentrated inheritance for the colonial period.","number":3}],"slug":"isaac-cowles-1675"},"X02764":{"id":"X02764","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Mary","last_name":"Cowles","maiden_name":"Andrews","married_names":["Cowles"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Mary Andrews Cowles"},"birth":{"year":1674,"month":12,"day":9,"city":"Farmington","county":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1708,"month":7,"day":19,"city":"Farmington","county":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"X00261","date_year":1694,"date_month":1,"date_day":2,"location_city":"Farmington","location_county":"Hartford","location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1708,"children_ids":["X02765","X02768","I00156","X00260"]}]